        <body>
            <pb n="1"/>
            <p rend="align(right)"><placeName>Mobile</placeName>
                <date>April 7 1851</date>.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)"><addressee>Rev I. Leeser</addressee>!</p>
            <p rend="indent(2)">Respected Sir!</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Enclosed please<lb/> find $20.00 it being nine Dollars
                subscription<lb/> of <persName>Israel H Jones</persName> &amp;c met. 4.00
                    <sic>arrearrs</sic> &amp; the subscription<lb/> for the ensuing year. Please
                take notice of the same<lb/> in the Occident. the Balance of 11.00 you will please
                give<lb/> me credit for the Thalith. Other <add>?</add> I have not yet<lb/> made.
                    <persName>Myer</persName> of <placeName>Montgomery</placeName> promises to send
                me 6.00 which<lb/> is all he owes bal. <persName>Philip</persName> is at present
                absent. You will do<lb/> me a favour by sending me a list of all your
                subscribers<lb/> &amp; their <sic>indebtness</sic>; I have written to <persName>Mr.
                    I Hart</persName>
                <placeName>N. O.</placeName><lb/> for a statement of Books I recvd<add>?</add> from
                him; &amp; if you will<lb/> let me know the amt you <add>?</add> from me for
                Books<lb/> I shall forthwith send you the Blln if there is any<lb/> I have been so
                careless that I have not taken any notice<lb/> of the money I sent you. The
                    <add>חדושים</add> I have not yet<lb/> disposed of, but <persName>Mr
                    Cohen</persName> told me last night that<lb/> he probably may take a
                    <sic>sett</sic>. You will send a copie<add>?</add><lb/> of the Occident to J.
                    <hi rend="underline"><persName>Loewenstein</persName>
                    <placeName>Marion Miss</placeName></hi>.</p>
            <pb n="2"/>
            <p><persName>Mr. L Lyons</persName> &amp; <persName>S. Levy</persName> of
                    <placeName>Mobile</placeName> whose names as<lb/> subscribers I
                    <sic>handet</sic> you when here, have not recd<lb/> the Occident. You may send
                me 1 doz copies of prayer<lb/> books <sic>german</sic> minhag &amp; 1 doz. spelling
                books. Send the same to <persName>Mr. C. Nussbaum</persName>
                <placeName>N. Y.</placeName> as I expect<lb/> Books <add>?</add> from him.</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">We are taken now action slips here of building<lb/> a synagogue. A
                lot is already purchased; building<lb/> will be <add>?</add> forthwith. The
                brickwork is to be<lb/> finished by next fall, when the basement which is<lb/> to
                serve hereafter for a schoolroom is to be <sic>fittet</sic><lb/> up for a temporary
                place of worship, to save any<lb/> farther rent. The whole when finished will cost
                about<lb/> $15.000. After which the cong will no doubt engage a<lb/> efficient
                lecturer if any are to be found. How would<lb/>
                <persName>Rev. I Leeser</persName> determine<add>?</add> if he should be solicit to
                tell<lb/> the Israelites <del>their sins</del> of <placeName>Mobile</placeName>
                their sins?<lb/> &amp; to lead them into they path of virtue &amp; religion.
                    <sic>if</sic><lb/> he would consent, I am sure the congn would
                    warmly<add>?</add><lb/> &amp; with our accord accept him as their pastor.<lb/>
                Consider the above not as a question to be answered<lb/> by you, they are merely
                random thoughts, but that<lb/> much I will say, that much good can be done here
                among<lb/> the Israelites, &amp; that a minister like the above named<lb/> &amp;
                may</p>
            <pb n="3"/>
            <p>effect much good &amp; I am sure they all would hail<lb/> such an event with the
                utmost delight &amp; pleasure I<lb/> rem more than your humble servant.—</p>
            <p rend="indent(1)">I am my dear sir</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">Yours very truly</p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <persName role="author">B H Emanuel</persName>
            </p>
            <p rend="indent(3)">
                <add>חזן שוחט מלמד שו"ש לק"ק ש"ש</add>
            </p>
        </body>
